Borno State House of Assembly has screened and approved 19 out of the 20 commissioner nominees sent to it by Gov. Babagana Zulum. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that Zulum, who dissolved his cabinet in May had on June 14, sent the list of 20 nominees, including 17 former commissioners, to the legislature. The screening exercise started on Tuesday with nine nominees while 10 nominees took their turns on Wednesday.   Ripples over 72 missing trafficked children from Taraba…     Fight killer-hersdmen back, Ortom tells Benue residents     Alleged N6b money laundering: Court orders Mompha’s arrest   The only female nominee, Hajiya Zuwaira Gambo, who is out of the country, could not appear for the screening. Gambo, the former Commissioner for Women Affairs and Social Development, is part of the state government team to Egypt led by Zulum for the third edition of Aswan Forum for Sustainable Peace and Development. The screening exercise was presided over by the Speaker, Alhaji Abdulkarim Lawan, and the Assembly adjourned it next sitting to July 22. (NAN)